name: Diana Kennedy
bio: Diana Kennedy is a British-born, Mexican-based chef, cookbook author, and culinary anthropologist. She is known for her extensive research into traditional Mexican cuisine and is considered an authority on the subject. Kennedy has written several books on Mexican cooking, including 'The Cuisines of Mexico,' 'The Essential Cuisines of Mexico,' and 'Oaxaca al Gusto,' which have all been critically acclaimed. Throughout her career, she has also been involved in the preservation of traditional Mexican cooking techniques and ingredients. Kennedy has been recognized for her contributions to Mexican cuisine and was awarded the Order of the Aztec Eagle, the highest honor bestowed on foreigners by the Mexican government.

recipes.name: Pozole
recipes.method: Boil pork and hominy with chiles, garlic, and onion until tender. Serve with chopped onion, lime wedges, and cilantro.

recipes.name: Chiles en Nogada
recipes.method: Stuff chiles with meat and fruit mixture, then top with creamy walnut sauce and garnish with pomegranate seeds and parsley.

recipes.name: Salsa Roja
recipes.method: Char tomatoes, onion, and chiles until blistered. Blend with garlic and cilantro until smooth. Season with salt and serve with tortilla chips.

recipes.name: Tamales
recipes.method: Soak corn husks, then spread masa on each one. Top with meat mixture and wrap tightly. Steam until cooked through.

recipes.name: Tres Leches Cake
recipes.method: Bake cake, then soak with three types of milk. Top with whipped cream and garnish with fresh fruit.

recipes.name: Pico de Gallo
recipes.method: Chop tomatoes, onion, and jalapeño. Mix with lime juice and cilantro. Season with salt and serve with tortilla chips.

name: Enrique Olvera
bio: Enrique Olvera is a Mexican chef and restaurateur who is considered one of the most influential chefs in Latin America. He is the owner and head chef of Pujol, a restaurant in Mexico City that has been ranked among the world's 50 best restaurants. Olvera is known for his creative and contemporary take on traditional Mexican cuisine, which often incorporates unusual ingredients and innovative techniques. He has also opened several other restaurants in Mexico and the United States, including Cosme in New York City. Olvera has been recognized for his contributions to the culinary world and has received numerous awards, including the Diners Club Lifetime Achievement Award and the Chef's Choice Award from Madrid Fusión.

recipes.name: Tacos al Pastor
recipes.method: Marinate pork in achiote paste and pineapple juice, then grill on a spit. Serve on warm tortillas with diced pineapple and onion.

recipes.name: Mole Poblano
recipes.method: Toast chiles and grind with spices and nuts. Simmer with tomatoes, onion, and garlic until thick. Add chocolate and stir until melted.

recipes.name: Ceviche
recipes.method: Marinate fish in lime juice until opaque. Mix with diced onion, cilantro, and avocado. Season with salt and serve with tortilla chips.

recipes.name: Chiles Rellenos
recipes.method: Roast and peel chiles. Stuff with cheese and dip in egg batter. Fry until golden brown and serve with tomato sauce.

recipes.name: Guacamole
recipes.method: Mash avocado with onion, tomato, cilantro, and lime juice. Season with salt and serve with tortilla chips.

name: Patricia Quintana
bio: Patricia Quintana was a Mexican chef, author, and television personality who was widely regarded as an authority on Mexican cuisine. She was known for her emphasis on traditional Mexican ingredients and cooking techniques, as well as her efforts to promote Mexican cuisine both domestically and internationally. Quintana owned and operated several restaurants in Mexico, including Izote and La Guapa. She also wrote several cookbooks, including 'Mexico's Feasts of Life,' which was recognized with the James Beard Award. Throughout her career, Quintana was involved in promoting Mexican cuisine abroad, and she was a frequent guest speaker at culinary conferences and events. She was also a judge on the popular television show 'Top Chef Mexico.' Quintana passed away in 2018, but her contributions to Mexican cuisine continue to be celebrated and recognized today.

recipes.name: Chiles en Nogada
recipes.method: Roast, peel, and seed chiles. Stuff with beef, fruit, and nuts. Coat in egg batter and fry. Top with walnut sauce and pomegranate seeds.

recipes.name: Pozole
recipes.method: Boil pork with garlic, onion, and spices until tender. Add hominy and simmer until cooked. Serve with lettuce, radish, lime, and tortilla chips.

recipes.name: Tamales
recipes.method: Soak corn husks in water. Mix masa with broth and spread on husks. Add filling of pork and sauce. Roll and steam until cooked.

recipes.name: Salsa Roja
recipes.method: Toast chiles and blend with tomatoes, onion, and garlic. Add cilantro and salt to taste.

recipes.name: Flan
recipes.method: Whisk eggs with milk, sugar, and flavorings. Pour into ramekins and bake in a water bath until set. Chill and serve.

recipes.name: Sopa Azteca
recipes.method: Blend tomatoes, garlic, and onion. Simmer with broth and chips until

name: Jiro Ono
bio: Jiro Ono is a Japanese sushi chef and owner of Sukiyabashi Jiro, a Michelin three-star restaurant in Tokyo, Japan. He is widely regarded as one of the world's greatest sushi chefs and has been credited with elevating sushi to an art form. Ono has been making sushi for over 70 years, and he is known for his attention to detail and his use of the freshest ingredients. His restaurant, Sukiyabashi Jiro, has become a culinary destination for food lovers around the world, and it has been the subject of the documentary film 'Jiro Dreams of Sushi.' Ono has received numerous accolades throughout his career, including being recognized as a 'Living National Treasure' by the Japanese government. Despite his international fame, Ono remains dedicated to his craft and continues to make sushi at his restaurant in Tokyo.

recipes.name: Sushi
recipes.method: Cook and season sushi rice. Cut fish into slices. Form rice into balls and top with fish. Serve with wasabi, soy sauce, and seaweed.

recipes.name: Sashimi
recipes.method: Cut fish into thin slices. Serve with wasabi and soy sauce.

recipes.name: Chirashi
recipes.method: Cook and season sushi rice. Top with sliced fish, vegetables, and egg. Serve with seaweed.

name: Gordon Ramsay
bio: A Maxican chef and restaurateur known for his fiery temper and high culinary standards. He has multiple Michelin stars and is a popular television personality, hosting shows such as 'Hell's Kitchen' and 'MasterChef.'

recipes.name: Beef Wellington
recipes.method: Wrap beef fillet in prosciutto and mushrooms, then wrap in puff pastry. Brush with egg wash and bake until golden brown.

recipes.name: Fish and Chips
recipes.method: Dredge cod fillet in seasoned flour, then dip in beer batter. Fry in hot oil until golden brown. Serve with chips.

recipes.name: Shepherd's Pie
recipes.method: Brown ground beef with carrots, peas, and onion. Top with mashed potatoes and bake until golden brown.

recipes.name: Beef Stroganoff
recipes.method: Saute beef sirloin with mushrooms and onion. Add sour cream and simmer until thickened. Serve over egg noodles.

name: Ina Garten
bio: Ina Garten is an American chef, author, and television personality who is known for her approachable, home-style cooking. She rose to fame with her popular cookbook 'The Barefoot Contessa Cookbook,' which has since spawned a successful food and lifestyle brand. Garten's recipes emphasize fresh, seasonal ingredients and simple, yet elegant presentation. She has written several other best-selling cookbooks, including 'Barefoot Contessa Parties!' and 'Barefoot Contessa Foolproof.' Garten has also hosted several cooking shows on the Food Network, including 'Barefoot Contessa' and 'Cook Like a Pro.' Throughout her career, she has been recognized for her contributions to the culinary world, including being inducted into the Culinary Hall of Fame. Garten continues to inspire home cooks with her recipes, cookbooks, and television appearances.

recipes.name: Lobster Mac and Cheese
recipes.method: Boil macaroni and lobster, then mix with a cheese sauce made from butter, flour, and milk. Top with breadcrumbs and bake until golden brown.

recipes.name: Beef Bourguignon
recipes.method: Brown beef and bacon, then add carrots and onions. Deglaze with red wine and simmer until tender.

recipes.name: Roast Turkey
recipes.method: Rub turkey with butter, garlic, lemon, and thyme. Roast until golden brown and cooked through.

recipes.name: Potato Salad
recipes.method: Boil potatoes, then mix with a dressing made from mayonnaise, sour cream, scallions, and dill.

recipes.name: Shrimp Scampi
recipes.method: Saute shrimp and garlic in butter, then toss with pasta and lemon.
